The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Ranchi, Aug. 4: Jharkhand High Court today directed the CBI to take over the assets probe against former chief minister Madhu Koda and seven of his erstwhile cabinet colleagues, almost two years after a PIL was filed seeking the intervention of the central agency.          
	A division bench of acting Chief Justice Sushil Harkauli and Justice D.N. Patel passed the order that effectively puts Koda, now Singhbhum MP, in a tight corner for alleged involvement in a multi-crore scam.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Private schools cannot claim exemption from disclosing information to the education directorate under Right to Information Act, the Central Information Commission has held, thus bringing them within the ambit of the transparency law.                   
	Giridih/Ranchi: Five employees of a private security agency were ki-lled in Pirtand, 25km from the Giridih district headquarters, last even-ing when CPI(Maoist) rebels blew up their SUV, apparently mistaking it for a police vehicle.                  
	Ranchi: The Jharkhand-Bihar Area Committee chief of the CPI(Maoist), Rajesh Srivastav alias Jai, was arrested in Ranchi on Wednesday by Intelligence Bureau sleuths. The 40-year-old was carrying a reward of Rs 5 lakh on his head.                  
	London (PTI): ,Britains postal service, the Royal Mail, has installed Indian-style squatting toilets after phasing out western-type commodes at its sorting depot in Manchester to meet the needs of staff with origins in the sub-continent.                                                                                                                                              
